"/> This is a common (and annoying) misconception. The job of someone
backing (or fronting) out from a parking space is not to do it so
that oncoming traffic has time to stop. The job of the person
leaving a parking space is to do it so that oncoming traffic doesn't
need to stop, not even to slow down.

In legal terms, you must yield the right of way when leaving a
parking space. That means you must not interfere IN ANY WAY with
vehicles already in the road.

